    "The formulation of the IPO loss function is in Equation 2 as follows:",
    "where x represents the input, y w denotes the preferred response, y l indicates the unpreferred response, π ref is the reference policy and τ is a real positive regularisation parameter.",
    "Although the IPO algorithm overcomes the problems of overfitting and the need for extensive regularization present in DPO, the approach of aligning based on two preferences has different complications.",
    "The KTO study seeks to enhance the effectiveness of the DPO method by implementing a strategy that utilizes only a single preference.",
    "This method is inspired by the Kahneman & Tversky theory, which observes that humans are more acutely affected by losses than gains of comparable magnitude."
